	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The editor is probably using 32-bit values for everything (first the dimensions of the map - $10 x $10 - and then the metatiles), even though you only want 8 bits. The 0s are probably the 24 bits you are not using.
<br />
<br />An existing editor will hardly output data in a format that's ready to be included in the ROM, most of the time you have to code a converter/plugin/whatever. Or maybe somewhere in the program you can configure it to use 8-bit values?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


